<h1 class="hero-h">What Is Claude Opus? <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Anthropic's highest-capability tier.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Claude Opus is Anthropic's flagship — most capable, most expensive, used when reasoning quality is non-negotiable. Here's where it fits and when it's worth paying for over Sonnet.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Claude Opus is Anthropic's most capable model — used for the hardest reasoning, most complex coding, and highest-stakes writing. Slower and more expensive than Sonnet; most teams use Opus selectively for complex tasks while running Sonnet as the daily driver.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Where Opus fits in the Claude family</h2><p class="body">Anthropic's three-tier family: Haiku (fast, cheap), Sonnet (workhorse), Opus (flagship). Opus is the largest and most capable.</p><p class="body">Opus is the model to reach for when you need the absolute best reasoning quality, even at higher cost and latency.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When Opus is worth the cost</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Complex strategic analysis requiring multi-step reasoning.</li><li>Code generation in large, intricate codebases.</li><li>Research synthesis across many documents.</li><li>High-stakes writing where the quality ceiling matters (legal briefs, financial analyses, board materials).</li><li>Tasks where Sonnet has tried and produced not-quite-right output.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When Sonnet is good enough</h2><p class="body">For the vast majority of business workflows — drafts, summaries, follow-up emails, content briefs, meeting notes, basic research — Sonnet matches or exceeds what you need. Reaching for Opus by default wastes money.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Cost considerations</h2><p class="body">Opus per-token cost is meaningfully higher than Sonnet. For production workflows running thousands of calls per month, using Opus everywhere can be 3-10x more expensive than using Sonnet with selective Opus escalation.</p></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Should my whole team use Opus?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Almost never. Default to Sonnet. Escalate specific high-stakes tasks to Opus.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is Opus available in Claude Team?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — Claude Team users can switch to Opus per conversation.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is Opus available through Claude Code?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — model selection is configurable in Claude Code.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How much smarter is Opus than Sonnet?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Meaningfully on hard reasoning tasks; marginally on everyday business writing. Test with your specific workflow.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Will Opus replace Sonnet?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No — they serve different needs. Anthropic ships new versions of both regularly.</p></div>
</div></section>

